comments.body:
@daveisfera I've been testing this on Fedora 30 and Fedora 31 and both 1.14.8 and 1.14.3 both are working for me.  I just realized that you're using "Amazon Linux" and that's not one I've used before.  Do you by chance have the ability to spin up a Fedora 30+ VM and see how it goes there for you?

The settings for the memory are handle by cgroup.  Do you happen to know if your linux uses cgroup v1 or cgroup v2?  Both should work, but you'd need to look at this for cgroup v2:

`cat /sys/fs/cgroup/$(sed -e 's|0::||' < /proc/self/cgroup)/memory.max`

@giuseppe if you have any thoughts, please chime in.
